The {{IAST|niggahīta}} is represented with the sign ං. Consonant sequences may be combined in ligatures in a manner identical to that described above for Sinhala.

As an example, below is the first verse from the [[Dhammapada]] in Pali in Sinhala script, followed by Romanization:

